---
import Layout from '../../layouts/Layout.astro';
import Navigation from '../../components/Navigation';
import Footer from '../../components/Footer';
import Chatbot from '../../components/Chatbot';

const lang = 'en';
const title = 'Terms and Conditions of Use of the Automatisons.fr website';
const description = 'Terms and Conditions of Use of the services offered by Automatisons.';
---

<Layout title={title} description={description} >
  <Navigation lang={lang} isHomePage={false} client:load />

  <main class="pt-16">
    <section class="max-w-4xl mx-auto px-4 py-20 text-gray-800">
      <h1 class="text-4xl font-bold mb-10">Terms and Conditions of Use of the Automatisons.fr website</h1>

      <p class="bg-yellow-100 border-l-4 border-yellow-400 text-yellow-900 px-4 py-3 mb-6">
        <strong>Important:</strong> These Terms and Conditions of Use (TCU) govern the use of the automation and artificial intelligence services offered by Automatisons. They constitute a contract between you and our company.
      </p>

      <h2 class="text-2xl font-semibold mt-8 mb-2">1. Purpose and Scope</h2>
      <p class="mb-4">
        These TCU define the conditions under which Automatisons provides its automation, artificial intelligence, and digital transformation consulting services. They apply to any order placed via our website, by phone, email, or any other means.
      </p>

      <h2 class="text-2xl font-semibold mt-8 mb-2">2. Definitions</h2>
      <p class="mb-4">
        <strong>"Automatisons" or "Provider"</strong>: the company SARL 36Blue<br />
        <strong>"Client"</strong>: any natural or legal person who orders services<br />
        <strong>"Services"</strong>: automation, AI, consulting, and training services<br />
        <strong>"Project"</strong>: all Services defined in a quote or contract<br />
        <strong>"Deliverables"</strong>: results of the Services provided to the Client
      </p>

      <h2 class="text-2xl font-semibold mt-8 mb-2">3. Orders and Acceptance</h2>
      <h3 class="text-xl font-medium mt-4">3.1 Order Process</h3>
      <p class="mb-4">
        Each order follows this process:
        <ul class="list-disc ml-6 mt-2">
          <li>Free audit (48h)</li>
          <li>Issuance of a personalized quote (within 7 days)</li>
          <li>Validation by the Client</li>
          <li>Signature of the contract</li>
          <li>Start of work</li>
        </ul>
      </p>
      <h3 class="text-xl font-medium mt-4">3.2 Acceptance</h3>
      <p class="mb-4">
        The order is final after the quote is signed and the deposit received. Automatisons reserves the right to refuse any order that does not comply with these TCU.
      </p>

      <h2 class="text-2xl font-semibold mt-8 mb-2">4. Prices and Payment Terms</h2>
      <h3 class="text-xl font-medium mt-4">4.1 Prices</h3>
      <p class="mb-4">
        Prices are in euros excluding taxes. Any additional service will be subject to a separate quote.
      </p>

      <h3 class="text-xl font-medium mt-4">4.2 Payment Terms</h3>
      <div class="overflow-x-auto mb-4">
        <table class="min-w-full border border-gray-300 text-sm">
          <thead class="bg-gray-100">
            <tr>
              <th class="border border-gray-300 px-4 py-2 text-left">Project type</th>
              <th class="border border-gray-300 px-4 py-2 text-left">Deposit</th>
              <th class="border border-gray-300 px-4 py-2 text-left">Balance</th>
            </tr>
          </thead>
          <tbody>
            <tr>
              <td class="border border-gray-300 px-4 py-2">&lt; €5,000</td>
              <td class="border border-gray-300 px-4 py-2">30% upon order</td>
              <td class="border border-gray-300 px-4 py-2">70% upon delivery</td>
            </tr>
            <tr class="bg-gray-50">
              <td class="border border-gray-300 px-4 py-2">€5,000 - €20,000</td>
              <td class="border border-gray-300 px-4 py-2">40% upon order</td>
              <td class="border border-gray-300 px-4 py-2">60% upon delivery</td>
            </tr>
            <tr>
              <td class="border border-gray-300 px-4 py-2">&gt; €20,000</td>
              <td class="border border-gray-300 px-4 py-2">50% upon order</td>
              <td class="border border-gray-300 px-4 py-2">50% according to schedule</td>
            </tr>
          </tbody>
        </table>
      </div>

      <h3 class="text-xl font-medium mt-4">4.3 Late Payment</h3>
      <p class="mb-4">
        In case of delay, penalties of 3% per month will be applied. After 8 days without payment, services may be suspended.
      </p>

      <h2 class="text-2xl font-semibold mt-8 mb-2">5. Service Execution</h2>
      <h3 class="text-xl font-medium mt-4">5.1 Deadlines</h3>
      <p class="mb-4">
        Deadlines are given for information purposes only and begin upon receipt of the deposit and all required materials.
      </p>
      <h3 class="text-xl font-medium mt-4">5.2 Client Obligations</h3>
      <p class="mb-4">
        The Client agrees to provide the necessary information and access, designate a contact person, and validate deliverables on time.
      </p>
      <h3 class="text-xl font-medium mt-4">5.3 Provider Obligations</h3>
      <p class="mb-4">
        Automatisons undertakes to work professionally, respect confidentiality, and provide support and training if agreed.
      </p>

      <h2 class="text-2xl font-semibold mt-8 mb-2">6. Intellectual Property</h2>
      <p class="mb-4">
        Specific developments become the property of the Client after full payment. Generic tools remain the property of Automatisons.
      </p>

      <h2 class="text-2xl font-semibold mt-8 mb-2">7. Confidentiality</h2>
      <p class="mb-4">
        Each party agrees to keep all exchanged information confidential for 5 years after the end of the contractual relationship.
      </p>

      <h2 class="text-2xl font-semibold mt-8 mb-2">8. Warranties and Liability</h2>
      <p class="mb-4">
        Automatisons guarantees the conformity of the Services to the defined specifications. Its liability can only be engaged in the event of proven fault.
      </p>

      <h2 class="text-2xl font-semibold mt-8 mb-2">9. Applicable Law and Jurisdiction</h2>
      <p class="mb-4">
        These TCU are governed by French law. Any dispute will be submitted to the competent courts of Paris.
      </p>

      <h2 class="text-2xl font-semibold mt-8 mb-2">10. Contact</h2>
      <p class="mb-4">
        For any questions, you can contact us at:<br />
        Email: <a href="mailto:contact@automatisons.fr" class="text-blue-600 hover:underline">contact@automatisons.fr</a><br />
        Address: 25 RUE TRONCHET 25-27, 75008 PARIS, France<br />
        Phone: +33 6 48 09 15 11
      </p>

      <p class="mt-12 text-sm text-gray-500">Last updated: June 24, 2025</p>
    </section>
  </main>

  <Footer lang={lang} client:load />
  {/*<Chatbot lang={lang} client:load />*/}
</Layout>
